Global Photoionization Detection (PID) Sensors and Detectors Market Insights
Photoionization Detection (PID) Sensors and Detectors Market size was valued at USD 0.64 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 1.11 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.3% from 2024 to 2030.

Photoionization Detection (PID) Sensors and Detectors Market Overview
The global Photoionization Detection (PID) Sensors and Detectors market has witnessed significant growth, reaching a market value of approximately $500 million in 2024. This growth is driven by increasing demand for gas detection systems in various industries, including environmental monitoring, industrial safety, and military applications. PID sensors are critical in identifying hazardous gases in the environment, contributing to workplace safety and environmental protection. The market is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6% from 2025 to 2030, driven by technological advancements and increasing regulatory standards in multiple sectors.

